    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-03T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6639: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-03T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 3, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 3—8:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>241. Mayer’s 224, January 16, 2 p.m., Consulate’s 64, May 1, 2 p.m.<note n="42"
                        xml:id="d276fn42">For telegram No. 64, see <ref target="#pg_150">p.
                            150</ref>.</note> Haas<note n="43" xml:id="d276fn43">Robert Haas
                        (French), director of the League of Nations communications and transit
                        section.</note> tells me that the China Technical Committee will be called
                    during the coming session of the Council in the week beginning May 14 and that
                    only the usual circular notice of convocation will be sent out. As Department
                    has made no comment of second sentence of paragraph 1 of Mayer’s 224, January
                    16, 2 p.m., I assume that I should attend the meeting in the capacity you
                    prescribed on receiving notice of the convocation. (Chinese-Japanese
                    controversy.)</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
